Review_Content: Good enough printer for the price. We had a 5000 series that was stellar for nearly 4 years, but needed to find something quick for some light printing. They still haven't been able to make printers that are easy to use - all these years later. But it looks nice and it works just fine so far

Review_Title: Nice but not dependable if turned off 24+ hours
Review_Content:
This is a nice printer, but if it is turned off more than a day, it has to be re-programed, set up again. I’ve had to call HP twice, spending about an hour each time. This is inconvenient and I’ve never heard that you can’t turn a printer off more than 24 hour without having to set up again. During hurricane season I guess we will have to re-set up every time we have to turn it off or lose power for more than 24 hours. They advised me if this continues, I may want to return it to Best Buy for exchange. 
However, the print is nice and fast and price is right.

If you don’t mind having to reconnect your printer every time you need to use it and you don’t mind picking up the manual 5 times a day to see what the flashing colored lights mean —-get this one! I think it was garbage. I’m Bummed too cause I really wanted to like it.

I thought about connecting it just with the good old reliable USB, but wait  it doesn't have a working USB port.  Also this model does not have any kind of display so if you want to know anything about whats going on.  you must  Print out a report... Useless if the printer won't print for some reason.   I purchasing a replacement already  for this Printer after only few Months.
